    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0004",
      "text": "Login and Service Parameters",
      "bbox": [
        114.0,
        57.38,
        271.54,
        69.64
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0005",
      "text": "6.1",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        82.97,
        109.88,
        94.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0006",
      "text": "Introduction",
      "bbox": [
        119.88,
        82.97,
        178.18,
        94.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0007",
      "text": "The Login procedure is a method by which an Nx_Port establishes its operating environment with a",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        106.97,
        539.95,
        118.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0008",
      "text": "Fabric, if present, and other destination Nx_Ports with which it communicates.  Fabric Login and",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        118.97,
        539.82,
        130.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0009",
      "text": "N_Port Login are both accomplished with a similar procedure using different D_IDs and possibly dif-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        130.97,
        540.1,
        142.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0010",
      "text": "ferent S_IDs.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        142.97,
        154.29,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0011",
      "text": "Login between an Nx_Port and the Fabric or between two Nx_Ports is long-lived.  The number of",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        166.96,
        540.01,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0012",
      "text": "concurrent Nx_Ports with which an Nx_Port may be logged in with is a function of the Nx_Port facili-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        178.96,
        539.99,
        190.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0013",
      "text": "ties available.  There is no one to one relationship between Login and Class 1 dedicated connec-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        190.96,
        540.17,
        202.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0014",
      "text": "tions.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        202.96,
        119.89,
        214.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0015",
      "text": "Login between an Nx_Port and the Fabric or between two Nx_Ports may use an explicit or implicit",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        226.96,
        539.98,
        238.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0016",
      "text": "method.  When Login is referred to throughout other sections of this standard, either the explicit or",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        238.96,
        540.01,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0017",
      "text": "implicit procedure may be used.  Implicit Login is assumed to provide the same functionality as Ex-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        250.96,
        539.89,
        262.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0018",
      "text": "plicit Login.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        262.96,
        145.96,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0019",
      "text": "Explicit Login is accomplished using a Login (FLOGI or PLOGI) ELS (see 4.2.7) within a new Ex-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        286.96,
        539.85,
        298.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0020",
      "text": "change to transfer the Service Parameters (contained in the Payload) of the Nx_Port initiating the Lo-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        298.96,
        540.13,
        310.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0021",
      "text": "gin Exchange.  The LS_ACC contains the Service Parameters of the Responder (contained in the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        310.96,
        539.83,
        322.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0022",
      "text": "Payload).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        322.96,
        138.2,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0023",
      "text": "Implicit Login is a method of defining and specifying the Service Parameters of destination Nx_Ports",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        346.96,
        540.0,
        358.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0024",
      "text": "by means other than the explicit use of the Login ELS.  Specific methods of implicit Login are not de-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        358.96,
        539.96,
        370.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0025",
      "text": "fined in this standard.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        370.96,
        191.05,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0026",
      "text": "Implicit Fabric Login, unlike Explicit Fabric Login, does not require the support, within an Nx_Port, of",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        394.96,
        539.97,
        406.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0027",
      "text": "the FLOGI Link Service request and reply.  Implicit Fabric Login may be supported in a variety of",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        406.96,
        540.03,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0028",
      "text": "ways, requiring varying levels of support within an Nx_Port.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        418.96,
        357.58,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0029",
      "text": "An Nx_Port determines its own native N_Port_ID through explicit or implicit Login by",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        442.96,
        467.63,
        454.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0030",
      "text": "a) the Fabric, if present,",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        466.96,
        216.22,
        478.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0031",
      "text": "b) implicit definition, or",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        490.96,
        210.11,
        502.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0032",
      "text": "c)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        514.96,
        114.35,
        526.07
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0033",
      "text": "assignment in the PLOGI Sequence transmitted to a destination Nx_Port attached in a point-to-",
      "bbox": [
        122.37,
        514.96,
        540.2,
        526.07
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0034",
      "text": "point topology.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        526.96,
        187.39,
        538.07
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0035",
      "text": "Nx_Ports may collect Address Identifiers from other potential destination Nx_Ports from:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        550.96,
        484.74,
        562.07
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0036",
      "text": "a) a name server function, if present,",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        574.96,
        273.56,
        586.07
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0037",
      "text": "b) implicit definition, or",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        598.96,
        210.11,
        610.07
      ],
      "block_index": 17,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0038",
      "text": "c)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        622.96,
        114.34,
        634.07
      ],
      "block_index": 18,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p152_s0039",
      "text": "an alternate initialization procedure.",
      "bbox": [
        122.37,
        622.96,
        280.13,
        634.07
      ],
      "block_index": 18,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    }
  ],
